# Purpose: Ignore local runtime data, virtual environments, caches, and editor artifacts.
# Input/Output: Used by Git to keep generated or sensitive files out of version control.
# Important invariants: Never commit `.env`, scan artifacts, database files, or Python caches.
# Debugging: If Git suddenly tracks generated files, update this list before cleaning the repo.

.env
.env.local
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
data/
htmlcov/
.coverage
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/
